SECTION 1 — DEFINITIONS (หมวดที่ 1 — นิยาม)

1.1 "Licensor" (ผู้อนุญาต) means Tirawat Nantamas and/or Dotmini Software,
    the original author and copyright holder of the Software.

1.2 "Licensee" (ผู้ได้รับอนุญาต) means any individual, organization, or
    entity that obtains a copy of the Software.

1.3 "Software" (ซอฟต์แวร์) means the MicroCode source code, binaries,
    assets, documentation, and all associated materials contained in this
    repository, including any modifications or derivative works.

1.4 "Derivative Work" (งานสืบเนื่อง) means any software, product, or
    service that is based on, incorporates, modifies, extends, or is
    substantially derived from the Software, in whole or in part.

1.5 "Commercial Use" (การใช้งานเชิงพาณิชย์) means any use of the Software
    or Derivative Work that is intended for or results in financial gain,
    monetary compensation, or commercial advantage. This includes but is
    not limited to:
    (a) Selling the Software or Derivative Work as a product or service;
    (b) Using the Software as part of a paid SaaS offering;
    (c) Integrating the Software into commercial products;
    (d) Using the Software to provide paid consulting or development services;
    (e) Generating advertising revenue from the Software or its derivatives;
    (f) Offering the Software as a managed or hosted service for profit.

1.6 "Personal Use" (การใช้งานส่วนบุคคล) means non-commercial use by an
    individual for personal learning, hobbyist development, research, or
    internal-only evaluation with no intent to generate revenue.

1.7 "Educational Use" (การใช้งานเพื่อการศึกษา) means use by accredited
    educational institutions, students, or educators for teaching, research,
    academic projects, or non-profit educational programs.

1.8 "Open Source Contribution" (การมีส่วนร่วมโอเพนซอร์ส) means modifications
    contributed back to the original Software repository and made available
    under this same license.

1.9 "Revenue" (รายได้) means gross revenue, income, or proceeds generated
    directly or indirectly from the Commercial Use of the Software or
    Derivative Work, before deductions for expenses, taxes, or other costs.

