    Educational Use within accredited institutions, provided:
    (a) This license and copyright notice are retained;
    (b) The use is genuinely non-commercial;
    (c) Proper attribution is given to the Licensor.

2.3 OPEN SOURCE CONTRIBUTION — Create and submit modifications, bug fixes,
    and improvements to the original repository, which shall be governed
    by this same license upon acceptance.

2.4 EVALUATION — Evaluate the Software for a period not exceeding 90 (ninety)
    days for the purpose of determining suitability for Commercial Use,
    after which a Commercial License Agreement must be executed.

2.5 ATTRIBUTION — In all Permitted Uses, the Licensee must:
    (a) Retain all copyright notices and license files;
    (b) Display the following attribution in any user-facing documentation:
        "Built with MicroCode — Copyright Tirawat Nantamas / Dotmini Software"
    (c) Not misrepresent the origin of the Software.

