SECTION 3 — COMMERCIAL USE (หมวดที่ 3 — การใช้งานเชิงพาณิชย์)

3.1 COMMERCIAL LICENSE REQUIRED
    Any Commercial Use of the Software or any Derivative Work requires a
    separate written Commercial License Agreement ("CLA") executed between
    the Licensee and the Licensor. Use of the Software for Commercial
    purposes without an executed CLA is a violation of this license and
    applicable copyright law.

3.2 REVENUE SHARING
    The standard Commercial License Agreement shall include a revenue-sharing
    arrangement as follows:

    (a) SMALL BUSINESS (Annual Revenue ≤ 10,000,000 THB / ~$280,000 USD):
        10% (ten percent) of Revenue generated from or attributable to the
        Software or Derivative Work, payable quarterly.

    (b) MEDIUM BUSINESS (Annual Revenue > 10,000,000 THB and ≤ 100,000,000 THB):
        15% (fifteen percent) of Revenue generated from or attributable to
        the Software or Derivative Work, payable quarterly.

    (c) ENTERPRISE (Annual Revenue > 100,000,000 THB / ~$2,800,000 USD):
        20% (twenty percent) of Revenue generated from or attributable to
        the Software or Derivative Work, payable quarterly.

    (d) The specific rate and terms may be negotiated on a case-by-case basis
        but shall not be less than 10% without written approval from the
        Licensor.

3.3 REPORTING OBLIGATIONS
    Licensees with a Commercial License Agreement shall:
    (a) Provide quarterly revenue reports within 30 days of each quarter end;
    (b) Maintain accurate financial records related to the Software's usage;
    (c) Allow the Licensor to audit such records with 30 days' written notice;
    (d) Revenue reports must be certified by a qualified accountant for
        Licensees generating Revenue exceeding 1,000,000 THB per quarter.

3.4 PAYMENT TERMS
    (a) Payments are due within 30 days of the end of each calendar quarter;
    (b) Late payments shall accrue interest at the rate of 7.5% per annum
        or the maximum rate permitted by Thai law, whichever is lower;
    (c) Payments shall be made in Thai Baht (THB) to the Licensor's
        designated bank account, or in USD equivalent at the exchange rate
        on the date of payment;
    (d) All applicable taxes (including VAT and withholding tax under Thai
        Revenue Code) are the responsibility of the Licensee.

3.5 HOW TO OBTAIN A COMMERCIAL LICENSE
    Contact the Licensor at:
    - GitHub: https://github.com/Dotmini
    - Organization: Dotmini Software
    - Website: https://spuaiclub.com
    - Email: Contact via GitHub

